In this article, President Donald Trump issues a proclamation declaring June 2017 as National Homeownership Month. He recognizes the benefits of homeownership to families, communities, and the nation, and emphasizes that owning a home is an essential element in achieving the American Dream. Trump acknowledges the decline in homeownership rates since the Great Recession and attributes it to weak economic growth, excessive regulations, and stagnant wages. He expresses his commitment to helping hard-working Americans become homeowners by working with Congress on reducing rules and regulations, cutting taxes, and eliminating unnecessary government spending. The goal is to strengthen the middle class and the American housing market, creating high-paying jobs and providing resources and freedom for Americans to fulfill their American Dream.